{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"alias":"fishy-cur-verve","description":"# S6-pre — GitHub mirror-lock pre-work (snapshot, ADR, backend/token scope)\n\n## Why\nThe GitHub mirror lock (S6) is a one-way-door change to a PUBLIC repo. De-risk it by doing\nthe no-live-repo-change pre-work FIRST: capture a restorable snapshot of the current\nprotection, record the decision + accepted risk in an ADR, and confirm the IaC backend +\ntoken scope — so S6's live apply is fast, ordered, and reversible. This story makes NO change\nto the live repo.\n\n## What\n- Snapshot the existing `main-protection` ruleset (DERISK E5: id 18048287 — `pull_request` +\n  `required_status_checks` + `deletion` + `non_fast_forward`, admins bypass-via-PR) to a\n  committed `infra/github/main-protection.snapshot.json`\n  (`gh api /repos/navapbc/rebar/rulesets/18048287`), so the prior PR-based protection can be\n  restored on rollback. Snapshot ONLY — the live ruleset is not modified here.\n- Write `docs/adr/0006-github-mirror-lock.md`: the repo-level-vs-org-level trade-off (free org\n  -> no admin-proof org-level rule; trusted-admin editability accepted), the DeployKey-bypass\n  `gh api` workaround (UI omits DeployKey; terraform-provider-github historically rejects it) +\n  its retirement path, and the one-way-door nature (replaces the human-PR model; disables\n  PRs/Issues/Actions).\n- Confirm the `Administration: write` token scope (fine-grained PAT scoped to navapbc/rebar,\n  injected as a `sensitive` Terraform var from a CI secret, never in `.tfvars`) and the shared\n  remote backend + state locking that S6 will use.\n\n## Scope\nIn: snapshot + ADR + token-scope/backend confirmation (NO live-repo changes). Out: creating /\nenforcing the rulesets + mirror hygiene (S6); the Gerrit-side replication (S5).\n\n## Files\n- `infra/github/main-protection.snapshot.json` (committed snapshot, for rollback)\n- `docs/adr/0006-github-mirror-lock.md`\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `infra/github/main-protection.snapshot.json` contains the full current definition of\n      ruleset 18048287 (captured via `gh api`), sufficient to recreate it on rollback.\n- [ ] `docs/adr/0006-github-mirror-lock.md` records the repo-level-vs-org-level trade-off, the\n      accepted trusted-admin-editability risk, the DeployKey `gh api` bypass workaround +\n      retirement path, and the one-way-door nature.\n- [ ] The required token scope (`Administration: write`, fine-grained PAT scoped to this repo,\n      injected as a `sensitive` var from a CI secret, never committed) is documented.\n- [ ] The shared remote backend + state locking that S6 will use is confirmed available; this\n      story makes NO change to the live repo (snapshot/docs only).","id":"dcea-1bae-4729-4700","parent_id":"d251-05e1-eb55-43b2","priority":2,"tags":["github","security"],"ticket_type":"story","title":"infra: S6-pre — GitHub mirror-lock pre-work (snapshot main-protection, ADR, backend/token scope)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1782692500904766001,"uuid":"b6ddfed4-b7b0-456e-9017-b85bf1b05b0a"}